cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with improving the random access channel mechanism for machine type communications in cellular networks, which falls under the category of networked and internet-connected systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves probabilistic modeling and analysis, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper deals with massive machine type communications, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
